Vice President met with the families of the Buffalo, New York shooting victims and expressed condolences for their unexpected loss. She emphasized the need to address the epidemic of hate and the rise in mass shootings, with over 200 incidents already this year. The Vice President called for unity and stated that harm against one person is harm against all of us. She mentioned previous tragedies in Atlanta, Orlando, and the Tree of Life synagogue, emphasizing the importance of diversity as unity. The Vice President discussed the personal tragedies of each family affected and the need for action to prevent such incidents. She advocated for measures such as an assault weapons ban and background checks to address gun violence. The Vice President called on Congress to take action and stressed the importance of a united nation.